cs.CR, cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.HC, cs.SOC

This paper discusses the threat model of trilateration and location privacy in location-based applications, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The study also involves testing popular dating applications, which could be classified under social and information sciences (cs.SI). The potential side channel attack fashion due to the current design of Jack'd could also be considered as a cybersecurity issue (cs.CY). The paper also raises concerns about user privacy, which could be related to human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and social computing (cs.SOC).
